Laſt, He lays at their dores the guilt of high treaſon againſt the Law of Moſes, in every part and parcel of it, though they ſeemd ſo much to cry it up, and wore broad Phylactories of it upon their Garments in their dayly Garb; and he circumſtantiates this guilt, by their breaking of the Law,Theophilact & Occumenius though received by the diſpoſition of Angels; Some refer this to


